# Anti-Pattern Catalogue

Detection signals and false-positive guards for each anti-pattern.
Read this file when a coaching observation in S5 or M6a requires deeper evidence assessment.

---

## 1. Repetition Without Resolution

**What it is:** The same pain point appears across multiple retros with no evidence of action, ownership, or change.

**Detection signals:**
- Pain point language is nearly identical across sessions (same words, same framing)
- The topic appears in the negative/pain frame in 3+ consecutive sessions
- No corresponding action item with an owner exists in any session
- Action items do exist but the pain point continues appearing despite them

**False-positive guards:**
- Some pain points are slow to resolve legitimately (e.g. org restructure, tool procurement). Do not flag as anti-pattern if there is evidence of active mitigation even without resolution.
- External dependency pain points (waiting on another team, waiting on budget) should be classified as systemic impediments, not as repetition-without-resolution — the team may be doing everything they can.

**Coaching significance:** This is the clearest signal that retrospectives are not driving improvement. The retro is functioning as a venting ritual, not a change mechanism.

